      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "BY request of Mayor Daggett,\nChief Waller last night relieved the\n\"a special policemen put on during\nthe w. w. P. strike excitement.\nThere was nothing for them to do\nand they have proved unsatis-\nfactory generally.\n\n\nTheir worst break was the ar\nrest Of Councilmen Phillips and\nHorn.\n\n\nThe city dads\" were discussing\nprivate affairs on the corner Of Riv-\nerside av. and Wall st. when the\nspecials hoped onto them for no\nother cause, apparently, than that\nthey were talking. The council\nmen were told to move on, and\nwhen they refused were arrested.\nThe specials when made to under\nstand who they were interfering\nwith dropped their prisoners like\nhot potatoes."
    }
  ]
